race.description: The Daily Advertiser Country Boosted Mdn Plate
race.comment: ROONAMI (10) looks ready to break through after two strong minor placings at Canberra. No tougher here and backing up quickly. Hitting her straps now and is the one to beat. NOIR VITESSE (1) made a cracking return off a long break on the Riverside, charging home to just miss over 1200m. Strips fitter and should enjoy the rise in trip, though second-up off a long layoff is a slight query. BELNERA (5) improved sharply last start when sent forward and can give another bold sight. HIP HIP OLE (9) boxed on well into fourth on debut at Bathurst, better for the run and keeps Keatings. Worth including. SUPER NIC (4) was midfield when resuming, steps up in trip and keeps McDougall. Each-way chance.
